This paper deals with natural language processing and vector space models, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves proof theory, which is a fundamental aspect of computer science and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of vector space models also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the Lambek calculus, which is a type of logic (cs.LO) and the paper's focus on ambiguity suggests a connection to computational semantics (cs.DS).
